Hal,

> PGP uses the Fermat test with bases 2,3,5, and 7, I think.  Does
> this ensure that the number is either prime or Carmichael?  Isn't

Since (as we all know ;) Carmichael numbers are pseudoprimes to every
base, I guess just testing 2,3,5,7 isn't good enough - meaning there
are probably composites which aren't Carmichael numbers that pass.

So testing with more bases will weed out these composites (except the
Carmichael numbers of course).


